==Production==
The series was created by Sean Jablonski, who had served as executive producer alongside Russ Krasnoff. It had been filmed in Atlanta.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://variety.com/2014/tv/news/usa-network-sets-summer-premiere-dates-for-rush-satisfaction-and-returnees-1201161441 |title=USA Network Sets Summer Premiere Dates for 'Rush,' 'Satisfaction' and Returnees |last=Kissell |first=Rick |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=April 23, 2014 |accessdate=2014-04-23 }}</ref>

==Reception==
The first season scored an 82% approval rating on Rotten Tomatoes,<ref name=rotten>{{cite web|title=Satisfaction Season 1|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/satisfaction/s01/|website=Rotten Tomatoes|accessdate=19 September 2014}}</ref> while scoring 63 out of 100 "generally positive" on [[Metacritic]] based on 19 reviews.<ref name=meta>{{cite web|title=Satisfaction: Season 1|url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/satisfaction-2014|website=Metacritic|accessdate=19 September 2014}}</ref>

==Broadcast==
''Satisfaction'' premiered on USA on July 17, 2014, at 10 p.m.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.deadline.com/2014/04/usa-network-summer-rush-satisfaction-royal-pains |title=USA Network Set Summer Premiere Dates |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=April 23, 2014}}</ref> In Australia, the series premiered on June 14, 2015 on [[Showcase (Australian TV channel)|showcase]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[TV Tonight]]|first=David|last=Knox|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2015/05/airdate-satisfaction-us.html|title=Airdate: Satisfaction (US)|date=May 21, 2015|accessdate=May 22, 2015}}</ref> Although it shared title with the earlier popular [[Satisfaction (Australian TV series)|Australian series of the same title]] and also dealt with the topic of escorting, the series is not related to this one in any way.

